text:
Based on the recommendations of the Scientific and Technical Committee on the necessity of strengthening the procedures of the state of health emergency and continuing to adhere to the measures and procedures necessary to address the virus #Corona #Covid19, the government decided, starting on Wednesday, December 23, 2020 at nine o'clock at night, for a period of 3 weeks, to take the following precautionary measures:
Closure of restaurants, cafes, shops and supermarkets at 8 pm;
Banning night movement nationwide, daily from nine in the evening until six in the morning, with the exception of special cases;
banning public or private parties and gatherings;
The total closure of restaurants, for a period of 3 weeks, in Casablanca, Marrakech, Agadir and Tangiers.
All previously announced precautionary measures will be maintained.

#Statement_of_the_government
The government decides to extend the period of work with the measures approved on Wednesday, December 23, 2020, for an additional week, starting on Wednesday, January 13, 2021 at nine o’clock in the evening, while maintaining the precautionary measures.
This decision came in the wake of the epidemiological development of the Corona virus - Covid 19 at the global level, with the emergence of new strains of this virus in some neighboring countries, and based on the recommendations of the Scientific and Technical Committee on the need to strengthen the procedures of the state of health emergency and continue to adhere to the measures and procedures necessary to address the Corona virus.
Precautionary measures concern:
1. Closure of restaurants, cafes, shops and supermarkets at 8 pm;
2. Prohibition of night movement nationwide, daily from nine o'clock at night to six o'clock in the morning, with the exception of special cases;
3. Prohibition of public or private parties and gatherings;
All previously announced precautionary measures will be maintained.
